1. “Don’t Gate It — Spread It” Loop (Core loop)
What happens

User sees event → clicks → shares → brings new user → new user lands on same event

How you build it

On EVERY event card:

Copy Link (primary)
WhatsApp (secondary)
Twitter (optional)

When they click:

Step 1
Instant feedback:

“Link copied. Send it to your people.”

Step 2 (this is the loop trigger)
Show 3 more events right after:

“More like this”
same city + category

👉 You turn one share into multiple sessions

2. “Group Decision” Loop (this one spreads fast)

People don’t go to events alone.

Build this:

Button on event:

“Send to group”

When clicked:

auto copies link
opens share sheet (mobile)

Then show:

“Who’s going with you?”

Options:

“Nobody yet”
“Waiting on replies”

👉 This creates:

repeated visits
re-sharing
decision-based loops
3. “Trending in Your City” Loop (fake it first)

Homepage section:

Trending in DC tonight

Don’t overthink it.

Start with:

most clicked
most viewed
most shared

Then:

Every click:

boosts that event

👉 This creates:

momentum
repeat checking behavior

People come back to see:

“what’s trending now”

4. “Miss It = Pain” Loop

This one drives urgency.

On event cards:

If event is soon:

“Happening tonight”

If passed:

“You missed this”

Then show:

“Next one like this”

👉 This creates:

FOMO
return behavior
future engagement
5. “City Identity” Loop (underrated)

People care about their city.

Every page should reinforce:

“DC events”
“DMV nightlife”
“Atlanta popping this weekend”

Then:

Add:

“Share DC with your people”

👉 Now users aren’t sharing events
👉 they’re sharing identity

6. “Save Without Account” Loop

No login. No friction.

When user clicks:

“Save”

Store in localStorage.

Then:

Next visit:

“Your saved events”

👉 This creates:

return visits
session continuity
behavior signals
7. “Creator / Promoter Loop” (this is big)

Give promoters a reason to push YOU.

For every event page:

Add:

“Promote this event with Scenario”

Give them:

share link
clean preview (OG tags already done)
optional embed (later)

👉 Now THEY drive traffic for you

8. “Infinite Discovery” Loop (Eventbrite style)

After every click:

You MUST show:

more events same city
more events same category
more events same date

No dead ends.

👉 This keeps:

session time high
clicks chained
signals stacking
9. “For You” Loop (lightweight version)

Don’t overbuild.

Track:

last city
last category

Then:

Homepage:

“For You”

Just reorder content.

👉 Feels personal
👉 drives repeat use

10. The Real Loop (how it all connects)

Here’s what you’re actually building:

User lands on event
clicks
shares to friend
friend lands on event
sees related events
clicks again
saves or shares
returns later

That’s it.

What matters most (don’t overcomplicate)

If you only build 3 things:

Share + copy link with feedback
Related events after every click
Trending section that updates

That alone creates loops.
